<br>
THE PLANES:<br>
<br>
Solusek Ro, The Burning Prince with his crown of flame and spear of fire rules the Plane of Flame from his mighty Burning Tower. Fire Elementals, Efreeti, and an assortment of other fire loving planar creatures inhabit Solusek’s endless kingdom of blazing landscapes under a burning red sky filled with clouds of smoke, smoldering embers, and fiery rain. <br>
<br>
The mortals attribute Solusek with such acts as the raising of the Serpent’s Spine Mountains and the destruction of Eldarr Forest, creating the Deserts of Ro and changing the face and history of Norrath. Does this deity, revered by powerful magicians throughout Norrath, serve the will of his father, the mysterious greater god Fennin Ro, Tyrant of Fire and Lord of the Plane of Fire? Or does Solusek Ro serve his own destructive and power hungry cause?<br>
<br>
Plane of Disease - The putrid stench of rotting flesh hangs heavy in the air as adventurers discover a vast plane of pestilence, decay, and corruption. <br>
Plane of Justice - A stark prison zone where the Tribunal sits in judgment. Adventurers will find the prison's orderly yet confining environment a challenge to chaotic souls.<br>
<br>
Plane of Nightmares - The home of Terris Thule. A forested region, a wilderness of terror, the Plane of Nightmares will steal the sleep of many adventurers.<br>
<br>
Plane of Knowledge - New Tanaan is a city-state that exists outside normal physical and political boundaries, a haven of knowledge for those who seek it.<br>
<br>
Plane of Tranquility - Tranquility, the gateway to deeper planar realms. Peace reigns supreme here and adventures will not be able to engage in combat or use offensive magics.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
FEATURES:<br>
<br>
<br>
Now players will soon be able to face the most powerful deities in all of Norrath. We are excited to announce the next installment in the best-selling, critically acclaimed EverQuest series, EverQuest: The Planes of Power™. <br>
<br>
An arcing storyline takes players on an epic adventure through the Planes of Power, home of the Gods of Norrath. Veteran players will face new challenges in each of up to 20 newly discovered planes. Players of all levels will benefit from the Plane of Knowledge that hosts scores of new quests and opens portals to Norrath making travel easier than ever. Hundreds of new items, quests and encounters will keep even the most veteran of players challenged and enthralled. <br>
<br>
Battle the minions of Rallos Zek in the Plane of War; help Karana regain control of the Plane of Storms; overcome vile pestilence in the Plane of Disease!<br>
<br>
You're in their worlds now!<br>
<br>
<br>
EverQuest: The Planes of Power Features List:<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Up to 20 new planar zones that push your teamwork abilities to the limit<br>
<br>
Hundreds of new items and monsters<br>
<br>
Exciting new quests and challenges await even the most experienced players<br>
<br>
Two planar cities that provide hubs for travel and player interaction <br>
<br>
A central storyline links the content from every zone into one compelling quest.<br>
<br>
Further character progression making players even more powerful<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
OTHER FAQs<br>
<br>
<br>
Are there more battle animations?<br>
Player animations will not be added in this expansion. There will be at least 50 new NPCs with unique animations.<br>
<br>
How many new playable zones are you planning to add?<br>
Twenty<br>
<br>
How will I get to the Planes?<br>
The planes will be accessed through numerous portals throughout the existing world.<br>
<br>
Like EverQuest: The Scars of Velious, will I need a level 35 character or above to play the game?<br>
The Plane of Knowledge will be available to players of all levels and will be a source of many new quests, making travel throughout Norrath far more convenient. All other new planar zones will require players to be level 46 or above to enter. <br>
<br>
How will this expansion engage a level 60 players who has played EQ for the last 3 years yet appeal to the "newbie"?<br>
Veteran players will enjoy new content that will provide months of exciting gameplay. Players of all levels will benefit from the Plane of Knowledge that hosts scores of new and challenging quests. There are plans to include several great features that will appeal to new players as well. <br>
<br>
<br>
BETA TESTING<br>
<br>
Will there be a beta? How do I get in?<br>
There will most certainly be a beta test; the requirements for acceptance have yet to be established.<br>
<br>
SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS<br>
<br>
What are the system requirements to run the game?<br>
Sony Online Entertainment does not plan to change the system requirements for The Planes of Power.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p><b>Kelliv Kyoukan
</b>
