<br>
Seriously, what I'm hoping is that VI allows anyone and everyone access to the Plane of Tranquility.  While the Plane of Knowledge sounds as if it will be very useful to players, one new zone isn't much for the low and mid level players.  Since there is apparently no conflict in the Plane of Tranquility, there isn't really any reason why low level players should not be allowed to go there.  Its not as if they can sit around and loot gear that has been left to rot.  Presumably, the zone will be full of quests, though, and I suppose its possible that VI will want to keep players from having the opportunity to complete quests and get gear that they shouldn't be having yet.<br>
At any rate, it will be interesting to see what kind of an effect the zone has on PvP servers.  There's no PvP allowed, and it apparently allows transit to other planes.  Presumably, people will be able to pop back and forth between Tranquility and other planes.  No matter who or what is pursuing you, its a safe haven (unless the zone has some weird rules concerning followers of Innoruuk and Cazic-Thule - zone faction, perhaps?  &quot;Plane of Tranquility teleports YOU to the next zone over.&quot; <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ).<br>
